content.problemStatement:
You're building a program to determine the ripeness of a fruit based on the number of days since harvest. Use `if-else if` conditions to categorize the fruit as `Unripe`, `Ripe`, or `Overripe`.

Consider the following C++ code:
```cpp
#include 
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int daysSinceHarvest = 6;

    if (daysSinceHarvest ___ 3) {
        cout << "Unripe" << endl;
    } ___ (daysSinceHarvest ___ 7) {
        cout << "Ripe" << endl;
    } else {
        cout << "Overripe" << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
```

